note._content: American flag suggested this may have been taken during Manly's celebrations for  the U.S. Great White Fleet visit in September 1908.However,the 'matching' photo taken from the wharf end of The Corso seems to date from c1912-13.These flags,lanterns etc. may be part of Manly's annual summer Venetian.
note.author: 39165494@N06

note._content: Corso tram tracks first laid in 1905 for Manly-to-Manly Lagoon route .
note.author: 39165494@N06

note._content: St Mathews Church of England,designed by Edmund Blacket(1865).Demolished,with neighbouring Victoria Hall,to widen The Corso for motor traffic and permit construction of the new St Mathews(1930) and its adjoining church-owned shops.
note.author: 39165494@N06

note._content: The Corso's Norfolk pines and successive other landscaping plans have now been supplanted by cabbage-tree palms(2009)
note.author: 39165494@N06
